  "explanation": "The defendant committed a serious breach of fiduciary duty by embezzling $25000 from their employer. However, the court must consider significant mitigating factors, namely that the defendant has no prior criminal record and has already made efforts to partially repay the stolen funds. While a harsh sentence is not warranted for a first-time non-violent offender making restitution, the breach of trust and the amount stolen require some period of confinement. A 6-month period of actual incarceration is appropriate to serve as a punishment and deterrent, which will be followed by a probationary period requiring full restitution of the remaining balance.",
  "verdict": 6
}
